    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hello everyone:\r\n\r\nI would like to have some feedback about this idea, and whether it is suitable for Tox.\r\n\r\nUsually, groups in messaging apps become flooded of messages that we are not necessarily interested in. My idea is the following: creating the possibility of adding tags to any message in a conversation. \r\nThese system would include the following features:\r\n\r\n•\tTags may be added to a message not just when it is sent, but anytime afterwards.\r\n•\tTags may be added to a message not just by the sender, buy by anyone in the group.\r\n•\tTags have a weight or rating, in such a way that different users may confirm that the tag is correctly associated to a message by voting that tag (i.e. through a “+1” button next to the tag).\r\n\r\nThen, messages could be filtered at any moment, by selecting one or more tags. Therefore, conversations could become organized while they are happening or afterwards.\r\n\r\nAny comments welcome.\r\nBest regards\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
